The USA amends the rules for the receipt of a visa
Persons must present themselves to the Visa Requests at the Consulate Council before their discussion; costs will be reduced in such a way.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying a visa in the Embassy of the United States and in the Consulates will change.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves in the Consulate at the Visa Request Services (ASC, the Initial Letters in English).
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant which are verified by the consulate before the discussion.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total costs for the processing of the visa are reduced because it is no longer necessary to pay separately the date agreement, the processing of the visa request and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall only make a single payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the counterparty of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visa for time workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visa shall not have to talk in the consulate, they must only present themselves at the nearest ASC where they present their documents and take their fingerprints.
Since the biometric data are collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the conversation in the consulate remain less time than before.
Those who request the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service charge of $26.
For additional information on the new visa application procedure, see http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
